text.tspan: Number of maternal deaths by region, 1990 to 2015
A maternal death refers to the death of a woman while pregnant or within 42 days of termination of pregnancy,
irrespective of the duration and site of the pregnancy, from any cause related to or aggravated by the pregnancy or
its management but not from accidental or incidental causes.
Source: World Health Organization (WHO)/UNICEF via the World Bank
